Exercise 04 — Valgrind: Memory Leak
======================================

The program runs and prints output without crashing.
But it leaks memory — some allocations are never freed.

Your goal: use Valgrind to find which allocations leak and why.

  Run with Valgrind:
    valgrind --leak-check=full --track-origins=yes ./target

  Read the output carefully:
    - "definitely lost" means memory that can never be freed
    - The report shows the allocation site (file + line number)

  Answer these questions:
    - How many bytes are leaked?
    - How many allocations are leaked?
    - Which lines in the source caused the leaks?

When you can answer all three AND have found the flag with GDB, submit it: horizon done HRZ{...}
